30|$|Open Educational Resources (OER) and Open Educational Practices (OEP) {{are making}} an evergrowing {{impact on the}} field of adult learning, {{offering}} free high-quality education to increasing numbers of people. However, the top-down distribution of weighty university courses that typifies current provision is not necessarily suitable for contexts such as Continued Professional Development (CPD). This article proposes that a change of focus from a supplier-driven to a needs-led approach, grounded in theories of informal learning, could increase the positive impact of OER and OEP beyond <b>the</b> <b>ivory</b> <b>towers</b> of higher education.|$|R
