40|$|This {{syllabus}} {{was submitted}} to the Rhodes College Office of Academic Affairs by the course instructor. We are symbol users and inhabitants of imagined worlds; we are also tool makers whose hands are “dirtied” in manipulating the world. 2 This course will pull us away from <b>the</b> <b>ivory</b> <b>towers</b> of our lofty untethered “thoughts,” which we often invest with determination of the lives we lead. (“Just put your mind to it. ” “It {{is a question of}} mind over matter. ” “Dream big!”) This course will moor us to an examination of our “materiality” and our engagement with the material world...|$|R
